  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the ttukbaegi earthenware cook to 300°F (150°C).",
    "Heat a tablespoon of oil in the cook over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion, carrot, and celery, and cook until the vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the haggis, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks.",
    "Pour in the beef broth and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.",
    "Stir in the flour to thicken the stew.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley."
  ],
